{"id": 225050000, "title": "Iran slams cutting off internet in Rafah Crossing", "text": "Kazem Gharibabadi, secretary of Iran's High Council for Human Rights, wrote on his X page, \" While Nikki Haley travels to occupied Palestine and writes a memorial on the bombs of the Zionist regime, this regime, in the absence of UN decisive action, has cut off the Internet in Rafah so that the people are deprived of even the narration of what happened to them these days\". Zionist officials have cut off communications and the Internet in Gaza\u2019s Rafah located near the border with Egypt. IDF also carried out raids in southern and western Rafah, bombing and shelling residential buildings in the city center. Israeli tanks were also stationed in the Yibna and Shabura refugee camps in southern Rafah, TASS reported. SD/6122317", "summary": "TEHRAN, May 29 (MNA) \u2013 Iran\u2019s top human rights official stated that the Zionist regime in the absence of UN decisive action, has cut off the Internet in Rafah so that the people are deprived of reporting what has happened to them these days.", "url": "https://en.mehrnews.com/news/215881/Iran-slams-cutting-off-internet-in-Rafah-Crossing", "image": "https://media.mehrnews.com/d/2024/04/15/4/4945871.jpg?ts=1713164009318", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 14:12:29", "author": null, "language": "en", "source_country": "ir", "sentiment": 0.065}